{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"nimble-teenage-aidi","description":"## What\nAdd agent-facing documentation to stop a recurring confusion: agents scoping \"batch writes to the local ticket store\" mistake the Jira reconciler's inbound commit-batcher for the general store write API, because the reconciler (`src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/`) is the ONLY place in the tree that already batches many event-files into fewer commits.\n\n## Why\nThe reconciler shares the low-level store lock (`src/rebar/_store/lock.py`, invariant I5) and the canonical-bytes contract with the local write path, so a grep for \"batch\"/\"commit\" lands there first. The stale epic cold-stall-chalk compounded this with its \"WS-B3: batch-apply\" wording. This has already misled at least one agent. Fix lands where an agent actually greps (module docstrings) plus one authoritative section.\n\n## Scope\n- Add a canonical \"Two writers, one store\" section to `docs/architecture.md` distinguishing the local store write path (`src/rebar/_store/event_append.py`; inline locked cores in `src/rebar/_commands/txn.py`) from the Jira reconciler (a CLIENT of the store), noting they share ONLY `_store.lock` + canonical bytes (no shared write API), flagging the reconciler inbound batcher as a Jira-sync internal (NOT a local batch-write API), and listing the overloaded vocabulary (reconcile / apply / batch / sync).\n- Add docstring signposts pointing to that section in `src/rebar/_store/event_append.py`, `src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py`, `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py`, and a one-liner near the batch commit in `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/__main__.py`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/architecture.md` has a \"Two writers, one store\" section covering: the two writers, what they share (lock + canonical bytes only), the trap (reconciler inbound batcher is a Jira-sync internal, not a store API), and the overloaded vocabulary.\n- [ ] Docstring cross-refs added to `src/rebar/_store/event_append.py`, `src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py`, `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py`, and `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/__main__.py`, each pointing to the section.\n- [ ] `make lint` and `make typecheck` pass (docs + docstrings only; no behavior change).\n- [ ] Change pushed to Gerrit for review with a `rebar-ticket:` trailer.","id":"f0df-2a45-8153-4da0","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"docs: disambiguate local ticket-store write path vs. Jira reconciler ('Two writers, one store')"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783647780389967001,"uuid":"7b1a6663-9574-4eb8-b492-ab310c151975"}